A few notes: The A7 in the chorus may not work with your singing. To me it sounds fine either way, keeping the straight A major triad or changing to the seventh. The modulation at the ending, for the key change to C, may sound strange. I believe the orchestra plays an augmented D, but not quite sure. It may also be Dsus4. A smoother modulation may be D Dm G7 F C, but youd probably need to insert an extra bar or two for all that. Then again, G to C is a short transition harmony- wise, so you can easily get away with just continuing the D major triad straight into the first C of the song ending. Lyrics in parentheses are the ladies singing in the back.
